reviews.review:
Overdue review.

Heard a lot of great reviews!  We've went for a special occasion, 'da 'ohana'!  And i am sad to say, i didn't take pictures of everything we had.  BUT 'da 'ohana' and I, we all enjoyed it!  Will definitely return and tell others, they gotta go!

MUST MAKE RESERVATION and we went early!  

Service - exceptional from calling for reservation, greeting, table service to exiting.
Food - everything we had was small portions, but there were all worth it!  Hope they will build that up when we come back.  
-fried rice;
-chow fun;
-beef broccoli;
-won ton soup;
-beef rib eye;
-clams;
-prawns;
-pork belly;
-a lot more
Drinks - tea, water, soda and we also ordered Wine.  Just prepare, they have a huge 3 inch binder of Wine/Champagne to order from.

Good thing we were on the way out after being there for over 1.5 hour.  Kenny Lee/Lees Liquor and his party started to show up for the back area and the bar area was starting to get jammed packed with people from the convention.

Plan accordingly.

Quiet at first, when we arrived, because they just opened.  Noisy when we were leaving.
